race.comment: YES LARRY (8) settled back after an awkward start before coming home strongly to score on debut over 1100m at this track two weeks ago. Promising type who can measure up again. HOLY CROWN (9) is finding it hard to crack another win but has been within range all preparation. Will find this easier than her last start fourth over 1300m at Rockhampton at 65 level. Gets another chance. SILENT ANGEL (12) went forward when resuming over 1000m at this track and held on well beaten just 0.7 lengths. Has to overcome a tricky draw but the longer sprint is likely to suit and a senior hoop goes on. SIDESHOW FRANKIE (4) resumed in the same race beaten 1.2L. He draws even wider but will be hitting the line. DEVOTED DEPUTY (3) also needs a good ride but he returned in solid order at the track and should be around the mark.
